thread.title: Stocks to watch on Thursday

author: news.com.au
title: Stocks to watch on Thursday
text:
STOCKS of interest on the Australian Securities Exchange on Thursday:
AMP - AMP - up nine cents, or 1.45 per cent, at $6.28
Financial services giant AMP's full year earnings are due out. APN - APN NEWS & MEDIA - down 0.5 cents, or 0.75 per cent, at 66 cents Trans-Tasman newspaper publisher and radio group APN News & Media releases its half year results. BXB - BRAMBLES - up 15 cents, or 1.5 per cent, at $10.33 Logistics giant Brambles' full year earnings are due out. ORG - ORIGIN ENERGY - up 50 cents, or 5.3 per cent, at $9.89 Energy retailer and oil and gas producer Origin Energy to release its full year results. QAN - QANTAS AIRWAYS - down three cents, or 0.8 per cent, at $3.76 Qantas Airways full year results are due out. TGR - TASSAL - up five cents, or 1.4 per cent, at $3.73 Australia's largest Salmon producer Tassal Group full year results are due out. TTS - TATTS GROUP - down five cents, or 1.25 per cent, at $3.96 Gaming giant Tatts Group's full year results are due out. WEB - WEBJET - down five cents, or 1.2 per cent, at $4.01 Online travel company Webjet full year earnings are due out. WES - WESFARMER - up 72 cents, or 1.8 per cent, at $40.38 Coles owner Wesfarmers releases its full year results
